{
  "stem": "12337.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You had to hold it like this, otherwise they would grab it out of your hand.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I was very fearful always of mice, and-- but you get used to it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Lice.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Like, unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We were covered with lice.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "By 3 o'clock you have to know we had no light at all.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The only light we had was between the slats of the wood.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And-- and in order for my father and mother and myself to keep sane, my father would teach me the Bible by heart.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I knew the whole Bible by heart.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Every day, you know, he would teach me something else.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And when he would forget a word I would remind him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So I became, like, very religious, always reciting something from the Bible.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And also Pavlo-- my mother asked for wool, and she started knitting.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I don't know how she was knitting with all the mice and the lice, but I don't know.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "She was knitting.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I remember her knitting all kinds of sweaters for the girls.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my father, [? he ?] wood [? boot. ?] And my father would carve shoes from wood.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Just to do something.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then the children would go to church, and everybody wanted to know, where did-- who made you those beautiful shoes and who made you-- you know?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He had to create all kinds of stories for that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they were busy up to 3 o'clock in the afternoon.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then it was pitch black.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this is how we survived.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It's-- it's-- like, if someone would come and tell me, I would never believe that anyone could live this way for 18 months, but we did.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We lived for 18 months with very little food, no water except just a drink to wet our lips, you know?",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
